128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 35198636}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229/comments/48718567.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229#comment-48718567"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 2229, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "Gazebo GUI crashes sometimes"}, "content": {"raw": "Was there ever any resolution to this? I get pretty much the same traceback around 20% of the time I start gazebo gui with ros (using kinetic on Ubuntu 16.04). \n\nX Error of failed request:  GLXBadDrawable\n  Major opcode of failed request:  154 (GLX)\n  Minor opcode of failed request:  5 (X_GLXMakeCurrent)\n  Serial number of failed request:  **45**\n  Current serial number in output stream:  **45**", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Was there ever any resolution to this? I get pretty much the same traceback around 20% of the time I start gazebo gui with ros (using kinetic on Ubuntu 16.04). </p>\n<p>X Error of failed request:  GLXBadDrawable\n  Major opcode of failed request:  154 (GLX)\n  Minor opcode of failed request:  5 (X_GLXMakeCurrent)\n  Serial number of failed request:  <strong>45</strong>\n  Current serial number in output stream:  <strong>45</strong></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-11-03T13:36:16.441829+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "jan stankiewicz", "uuid": "{2693f158-088c-45f9-b8f1-39c5f5449340}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2693f158-088c-45f9-b8f1-39c5f5449340%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2693f158-088c-45f9-b8f1-39c5f5449340%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/720b19a4a6bb6352f2c66269dc337d65d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJS-3.png"}}, "nickname": "jannsta1", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6e5a83ff-b991-4ec7-8233-cfc480c63c65"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 48718567}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229/comments/51117464.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229#comment-51117464"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 2229, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "Gazebo GUI crashes sometimes"}, "content": {"raw": "I encountered the same error\n\n```\n#!bash\nX Error of failed request:  GLXBadDrawable\n  Major opcode of failed request:  154 (GLX)\n  Minor opcode of failed request:  5 (X_GLXMakeCurrent)\n  Serial number of failed request:  45\n  Current serial number in output stream:  45\n\n```\nand, after finding this thread, I used ```sudo gazebo`` and the error is gone.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I encountered the same error</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-bash\"><pre><span></span>X Error of failed request:  GLXBadDrawable\n  Major opcode of failed request:  <span class=\"m\">154</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span>GLX<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n  Minor opcode of failed request:  <span class=\"m\">5</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span>X_GLXMakeCurrent<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n  Serial number of failed request:  <span class=\"m\">45</span>\n  Current serial number in output stream:  <span class=\"m\">45</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>and, after finding this thread, I used <code>`sudo gazebo</code> and the error is gone.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-03-13T00:56:32.456480+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Manuel L\u00f3pez", "uuid": "{ec735b56-5323-44e4-a6c7-b8ffc427489b}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bec735b56-5323-44e4-a6c7-b8ffc427489b%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bec735b56-5323-44e4-a6c7-b8ffc427489b%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1d856e4780be97f41a8413f5436bfc4fd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsML-3.png"}}, "nickname": "manuel-volans-i", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2302b03b-eeaa-4a82-bc07-fcb5d37c2338"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 51117464}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229/comments/53657474.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229#comment-53657474"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 2229, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "Gazebo GUI crashes sometimes"}, "content": {"raw": "Manuel, I\u2019m guessing that the root user had different environment variables set and that\u2019s why sudo worked.  Is there any chance you could post the diff between the environments?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Manuel, I\u2019m guessing that the root user had different environment variables set and that\u2019s why sudo worked.  Is there any chance you could post the diff between the environments?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-08-29T15:34:45.497402+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Daniel Hook", "uuid": "{6896b5b0-d9f1-4eec-8c4c-15adae0b9c7b}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B6896b5b0-d9f1-4eec-8c4c-15adae0b9c7b%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B6896b5b0-d9f1-4eec-8c4c-15adae0b9c7b%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ae17e294f2fe8bdd115fefa93aa5ca95d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsDH-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Daniel Hook", "type": "user", "account_id": "5d67ef95f506de0b6ce3ad5a"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 53657474}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229/comments/56278194.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229#comment-56278194"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 2229, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "Gazebo GUI crashes sometimes"}, "content": {"raw": "Still the same error here: \\(Ubuntu 16.04 with ROS-Kinetic and **Gazebo 9.11 \u2192 Update in this Bugtracker**\\) \n\n```plaintext\nX Error of failed request:  GLXBadDrawable\n  Major opcode of failed request:  154 (GLX)\n  Minor opcode of failed request:  5 (X_GLXMakeCurrent)\n  Serial number of failed request:  45\n  Current serial number in output stream:  45\nterminate called after throwing an instance of 'boost::exception_detail::clone_impl<boost::exception_detail::error_info_injector<boost::lock_error> >'\nterminate called recursively\nAborted (core dumped)\n```\n\n\u200c\n\nI get this error 20-30% of the time, when I try to launch Gazebo.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Still the same error here: (Ubuntu 16.04 with ROS-Kinetic and <strong>Gazebo 9.11 \u2192 Update in this Bugtracker</strong>) </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-plaintext\"><pre><span></span>X Error of failed request:  GLXBadDrawable\n  Major opcode of failed request:  154 (GLX)\n  Minor opcode of failed request:  5 (X_GLXMakeCurrent)\n  Serial number of failed request:  45\n  Current serial number in output stream:  45\nterminate called after throwing an instance of &#39;boost::exception_detail::clone_impl&lt;boost::exception_detail::error_info_injector&lt;boost::lock_error&gt; &gt;&#39;\nterminate called recursively\nAborted (core dumped)\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>\u200c</p>\n<p>I get this error 20-30% of the time, when I try to launch Gazebo.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-02-23T11:37:23.259489+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "1", "uuid": "{5bc8b0ed-6392-4512-a65d-c771d75758d2}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5bc8b0ed-6392-4512-a65d-c771d75758d2%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5bc8b0ed-6392-4512-a65d-c771d75758d2%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/073dea9171aa38a18c67cae057b79bb1d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netdefault-avatar-5.png"}}, "nickname": "1", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:3b259b42-e08b-4551-a2dc-e46ee7c30aff"}, "updated_on": "2020-02-23T11:40:56.168468+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 56278194}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229/comments/56740735.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229#comment-56740735"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/2229.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 2229, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "Gazebo GUI crashes sometimes"}, "content": {"raw": "I\u2019m seeing this on 18.04 with Gazebo 9.0.0 from the Ubuntu debians. Fresh install \\(after working around #2607 \\)  \nNvidia drivers \\(390.116\\) and glx is installed and working. Quadro P4000, output of glxinfo | grep render is pretty long and on a  different machine than the one I\u2019m posting from.  \n  \nI launched Gazebo 9.0.0  ten times using using ros launch, and it crashed 3 times with the same error as the comment above.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I\u2019m seeing this on 18.04 with Gazebo 9.0.0 from the Ubuntu debians. Fresh install (after working around <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2607/error-restcc-205-during-startup-gazebo\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Error [REST.cc:205] during startup gazebo\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#2607</s></a> )<br />\nNvidia drivers (390.116) and glx is installed and working. Quadro P4000, output of glxinfo | grep render is pretty long and on a  different machine than the one I\u2019m posting from.  </p>\n<p>I launched Gazebo 9.0.0  ten times using using ros launch, and it crashed 3 times with the same error as the comment above.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-03-31T18:09:40.149215+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Alexander Moriarty", "uuid": "{139b5c5b-dcd7-4d65-bc0c-192330283412}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B139b5c5b-dcd7-4d65-bc0c-192330283412%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B139b5c5b-dcd7-4d65-bc0c-192330283412%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/277dfce80ca37a1a62dceda47328d271d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsAM-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Alexander Moriarty", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:fe87eec5-99fd-49f6-9a4b-d5d9276f39eb"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 56740735}], "page": 1, "size": 13}